text: Jessica Ziu (born 6 June 2002) is an Irish footballer who plays as a Midfielder for Shelbourne Ladies and has appeared for the Republic of Ireland women's national team. ==Career== Jessica Ziu was born on 6 June 2002 and is from Dublin, Ireland. Ziu has been capped for the Republic of Ireland national team, appearing for the team during the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup qualifying cycle. Ziu has 3 Senior caps for her country from the age of 16. Ziu has been capped twice for the u15s Ireland team, twice for the u16s Ireland team, three times for the U17s while being called up to the U17s finals at just the age of 14 being one of the youngest players to participate in the tournament she currently has a u19 cap. Ziu has won herald sports player of the year being one of the youngest to ever participate in it. In 2019 she was voted u16 Ireland player of the year. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:Republic of Ireland women's association footballers Category:Republic of Ireland women's international footballers Category:Women's association football forwards Category:Shelbourne F.C.
